    active_lock_reason: null,
    body: 'I\'m moving from Next.js to CRA and my application contains a lot of debug calls which need to be removed at compile time (using dead code elimination). Since there are a lot of these calls across the application, I\'m looking for the most concise and clean way of writing them. Currently a call looks like this:\r\n\r\n`DEV && trace("message")`\r\n\r\nwhere `DEV` is defined at compile time using DefinePlugin, thus enabling the compiler to remove it in non development environments.\r\n\r\nI\'m looking for the same behavior in CRA (where access to DefinePlugin is not directly available), since writing `process.env.REACT_APP_DEV && trace("message")` a lot of times would be more time consuming and it would make the code a lot harder to read.\r\n\r\nThanks\r\n',
